<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Matta</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">intendente of Valparaiso</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of Foreign Relations</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-26"><hi rend="italic">October 26,
                                1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="center">D.</p>
                        <p>I herewith send you an extract from a communication which has this day
                            been addressed to this department by the United States minister,
                            relative to the disturbance with seamen belonging to the cruiser <hi rend="italic">Baltimore</hi>.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to send to this department, as speedily as possible, a report
                            of the examination held concerning this matter, the documents snowing
                            the origin and state of the investigation, if the examination is not
                            concluded, and such other antecedents as may show the course which has
                            been pursued by the local authorities.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">M. A. Matta</hi>.</p>
                        <p>Correct.</p>
                        <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">A. Bascuñan</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Intendente</hi>.</p>
                        <p>The foregoing agrees with the document on file at this legation.</p>
                        <closer>[<hi rend="smallcaps">l. s</hi>.] <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Aníbal Cruz</hi>.</signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <dateline rendition="#left"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-19"><hi rend="italic">December 19,
                                    1891</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>